.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH evade 1  "evade " 
.SH NAME
evade \- Transform a payload with evasion techniques
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBevade\fR <\fB\-\-payload\fR> [\fB\-\-level\fR] [\fB\-\-encoding\-only\fR] [\fB\-\-only\fR] [\fB\-\-exclude\fR] [\fB\-o\fR|\fB\-\-output\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Transform a payload with evasion techniques
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-payload\fR \fI<PAYLOAD>\fR
Payload to mutate and encode
.TP
\fB\-\-level\fR \fI<LEVEL>\fR [default: medium]
Evasion intensity
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
light
.IP \(bu 2
medium
.IP \(bu 2
heavy
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-encoding\-only\fR
Apply encoding only, without grammar\-aware mutations. (Shorthand for `\-\-exclude grammar`.)
.TP
\fB\-\-only\fR \fI<ONLY>...\fR
Restrict to listed technique paths (comma\-separated; e.g. `encoding/url,grammar`). Run `wafrift techniques list` for paths
.TP
\fB\-\-exclude\fR \fI<EXCLUDE>...\fR
Drop listed technique paths (comma\-separated; e.g. `encoding/url/triple,smuggling`)
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\fR \fI<OUTPUT>\fR
Write output to a file instead of stdout
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
